---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageIntro from "../components/PageIntro.astro";
import { withBase } from "../config/content";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Dustooned.">
  <div class="content-shell">
    <PageIntro
      title="About"
      eyebrow="¡Saludos!"
      description="Artist, educator, and community builder working across comics, animation, design, and interactive media."
    />
    <div class="document-actions" aria-label="Professional documents">
      <a class="button-link" href={withBase("/cv")}>CV</a>
      <a class="button-link" href={withBase("/resume")}>Resume</a>
    </div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        T' is a queer Cuban-Nicaraguan artist working across comics, animation, design, game and interactive
        development, and education. The work operates from the conviction that art is not a privilege but a right,
        functioning as a means of community empowerment through creative expression.
      </p>

      <h2>As a Storyteller</h2>
      <p>
        T' explores identity and justice by drawing from personal heritage and experience, connecting individual
        memory to wider cultural issues. The practice embraces experimentation through surrealism and innovation to
        challenge conventions and expand storytelling possibilities — balancing honoring tradition with a
        provocative reimagining of potential futures.
      </p>

      <h2>As an Educator</h2>
      <p>
        Guided by the principle "Art is Your Right," T' builds student-centered programs that position creativity
        as a practice of freedom. Experience teaching artists across age groups has shaped both effective methods
        and an understanding of what motivates creative reclamation. The educational mission centers on developing
        independent creators who become community builders within a broader cultural discourse.
      </p>

      <h2>Core Philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        Creativity connects us. Art serves at once as cultural memory and experimental practice — honoring
        formative histories while exploring surreal, provocative, unimagined territory. Through teaching,
        storytelling, and collaboration, the goal is to build accessible spaces where voices amplify and others
        reclaim creative agency.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
